    phaseImage: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 4cda1f626bf468b49a2bf6817e611bc5, type: 3}
    phaseDesc: 'The backpack felt like it weighed seven hundred pounds. Every bony
      protuberance in my feet was blistered beyond relief. Catching a glimpse of
      my reflection in the water, I saw a disheveled, dusty traveler looking back.
      As a pastor''s daughter, the biblical Exodus story I had heard since childhood
      seemed almost funny. How did close to a million Israelite families leave Egypt
      and hike for forty years, when I could barely handle three days?  '
