    phaseImage: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 1023675c72cab794788c901eb459c450, type: 3}
    phaseDesc: 'Was it a good idea to embark on a 20-mile backpacking trip when I
      couldn''t run a mile without stopping? The question seemed to answer itself.
      I had gone from sea level to an eleven-thousand-foot elevation within a day
      and my lungs let me know of it. With chapped lips, bruised arms, and a sunburned
      face I stood out like a sore thumb in the crowd of experienced hikers. Every
      painful step or sharp inhale asked the same question.  Why, I implored myself,
      did you say yes to something you were so underqualified for? '
